    Date: 27 Nov 87 04:53:26 GMT
    From: brian@sdcsvax.ucsd.edu  (Brian Kantor)

    It seems to me that perhaps we're putting the cart before the horse
    here if the argument is whether we're to maintain mailbox.domain
    because dots are part of the domain name system or whether it should be
    compatable with mailbox@host naming.

    Are we trying to differentiate the two kinds of addresses in order to
    determine whether the domain name system should be invoked or not?
    E.g., we'd make some sort of MB or MR or MAILA inquiry if the mail is
    addressed to brian.ucsd.edu but not if it's addressed as brian@ucsd.edu?  
    That seem off-base to me!
	...

What I'm trying to do is differentiate the two kinds of addresses to
determine HOW the naming system should be invoked.  mailbox.domain asks
"How do I deliver to this user" and mailbox@domain asks "How do I
deliver to this maildrop."

